<div id="learnabout">
 <h2>Learn about Actuated Valves & Controls</h2>
  <a href="/category/ball-valve"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_1.jpg" alt="Ball Valve" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/ball-valve" title="Ball Valves">Ball Valve</a></div>
 <div>Ball valves provide an economical and reliable method of controlling on-­off flow in a pipe line. Rotating the ball 90° opens or closes the flow passage. The ball valve can be operated with an electric actuator, air actuator or hand lever. Advantages of ball valves over other type valves may include: higher flows with less pressure drop, higher pressures, higher temperatures, straight through flow path and wider media compatibility.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/stainless-3-way-ball-valves"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_2.jpg" alt="3-Way Ball Valve" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/stainless-3-way-ball-valves" title="3-Way Ball Valves">3-Way Ball Valve</a></div>
  <div>Three port ball valves are available in either an L or T  shaped flow pathway through the ball. One quarter turn of the ball changes the valve position. Multiport 3-­way valve allows for mixing, bypassing or use as a diverter valve.</div><br /><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/pvc-ball-valves"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_3.jpg" alt="PVC Valve" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/pvc-ball-valves" title="PVC Valves">PVC Valve</a></div>
  <div>The PVC thermoplastic ball valve is generally used for on-­off control of water and other approved chemicals. PVC has been used successfully for over 60 years, and is highly resistant to corrosion. Rotating the ball 90 degrees opens or closes the PVC ball valve.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/stainless-flanged-ball-valves"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_4.jpg" alt="Flanged Ball Valve" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/stainless-flanged-ball-valves" title="Flanged Ball Valves">Flanged Ball Valve</a></div>
  <div>Flanged ball valves are installed in a pipe line with standard ANSI/ASME type flange mounting and used to turn  flow on and off. The flange ball valve eliminates pipe threads and allows for easy removal from the pipe line for  maintenance.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/actuated-ball-valve"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_5.jpg" alt="Valworx Ball Valve" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/actuated-ball-valve" title="Valworx Ball Valves">Valworx Ball Valve</a></div>
  <div>Valworx is a valve manufacturer and valve distributor of actuated valves and controls. Specialists in direct mount ball valves operated with either an electric actuator, pneumatic actuator or manual hand lever. Ball valves are  stocked in brass, PVC or 316 stainless steel for same day shipment.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/apollo-valves"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_6.jpg" alt="Apollo Valve" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/apollo-valves" title="Apollo Valves">Apollo Valve</a></div>
  <div>Apollo Valve Conbraco Industries, also known as Apollo Valve, manufactures a large selection of ball valves and other plumbing products. When you specify Apollo valves, you can count on quality products, engineered and designed for safety  and outstanding performance.</div><br /><br />

 <h2>Butterfly Valve</h2>

  <a href="/category/butterfly-valves"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_7.jpg" alt="Butterfly Valves" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/butterfly-valves" title="Butterfly Valve">Butterfly Valves</a></div>
  <div>A butterfly valve typically mounts between two pipe flanges and utilizes a quarter turn disc for turning flow on and  off. The lug butterfly valve has mounting threads built into the body for attaching to the flanges. The wafer butterfly valve mounts to a set of pipe flanges with through bolts.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/actuated-valve"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_8.jpg" alt="Actuated Butterfly Valves" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/actuated-valve" title="Actuated Butterfly Valve">Actuated Butterfly Valves</a></div>
  <div>Ductile iron and PVC butterfly valves are available with an electric actuator or an air actuator. The valve actuator is  direct mounted to the butterfly valve, eliminating the need for brackets, offering a significant cost savings. The actuated butterfly valve is available with a valve positioner, position limit switches and other accessories.</div><br /><br />

 <h2>Valve Actuator</h2>

  <a href="/category/5610-series-electric-actuators"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_9.jpg" alt="Electric Actuator" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/5610-series-electric-actuators" title="Electric Actuators">Electric Actuator</a></div>
  <div>Valworx electric actuators use a motor and gear box to rotate an output drive. This output drive is used to open and  close ball valves, butterfly valves and other devices. Valves can be direct mounted to actuators via the standard ISO5211 interface, eliminating the cost of mounting brackets. DPS valve positioner and BSR battery spring return options are available.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/5301-series-pneumatic-actuators-spring-return"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_10.jpg" alt="Pneumatic Actuator" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/5301-series-pneumatic-actuators-spring-return" title="Pneumatic Actuators">Pneumatic Actuator</a></div>
  <div>Rack and pinion quarter turn air actuators provide a simple and reliable method of automating ball valves and butterfly valves. Actuators are available in spring return or double acting.  Spring return actuators use air pressure to open  and springs to close the valve (failsafe). A double acting air actuator uses air to open and air to close.</div><br /><br />

 <h2>Solenoid Valve</h2>

  <a href="/category/solenoid-valve"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_11.jpg" alt="Solenoid Valve" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/solenoid-valve" title="Solenoid Valves">Solenoid Valve</a></div>
  <div>Solenoid Valves are used to control the flow of air, gas, water, oil, steam and other clean flowing media. A solenoid  valve offers fast and safe switching, high reliability and long service life. They offer excellent media compatibility  with low power requirements and a compact design.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/asco-valve"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_12.jpg" alt="ASCO Valve" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/asco-valve" title="ASCO Valves">ASCO Valve</a></div>
  <div>Asco Valve is a leading valve manufacturer of solenoid valves and controls. Asco products are designed to control  the flow of air, gas, water, oil and steam. Asco Red Hat solenoid valves cover the range from two position on/off  valves to entire flow control solutions. The Asco solenoid is widely known for exceptional quality and long service life.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/asco-repair-kits-rebuild-kits-parts"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_13.jpg" alt="ASCO Valve Parts" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/asco-repair-kits-rebuild-kits-parts" title="ASCO Valve Part">ASCO Valve Parts</a></div>
  <div>Easily find and buy hundreds of Asco solenoid valve rebuild kits and replacement coils. If you need additional help finding the correct replacement parts, contact Valworx at 1-­800-­511-­0100 or sales@valworx.com.</div><br /><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/asco-valves-solenoid-valves"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_14.jpg" alt="ASCO Solenoid Valve" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/asco-valves-solenoid-valves" title="ASCO Solenoid Valves">ASCO Solenoid Valve</a></div>
  <div>The Asco solenoid valve is used to control the flow of air, gas, water, oil, steam and other clean flowing media.  Asco valves are available as a 2-­way valve, 3-­way valve or 4-­way valve. The Asco solenoid is one of the most rugged and durable  coils available anywhere in industry.</div><br /><br />

 <h2>Pressure Gauge</h2>

  <a href="/category/pressure-gauge"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_15.jpg" alt="Pressure Gauge" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/pressure-gauge" title="Pressure Gauges">Pressure Gauge</a></div>
  <div>What is a pressure gauge? Pressure gauges are instruments used to measure the pressure of a gas or liquid. The  dial pressure gauge with a needle pointer is the most common and economical. Digital gauges are more costly, but  typically more accurate and easier to read. Common applications include use as a water pressure gauge, air pressure gauge, vacuum gauge and test gauge.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/wika-gauges"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_16.jpg" alt="Wika Pressure Gauge" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/wika-gauges" title="Wika Pressure Gauges">Wika Pressure Gauge</a></div>
  <div>Wika Instrument has continuously advanced pressure gauge, pressure transmitter and temperature measurement  instrumentation for over 60 years. Wika produces over 43 million pressure gauges, diaphragm seals, pressure  transmitters and thermometers worldwide annually. The Wika product line provides measuring solutions for most applications.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/pressure-gauges"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_18.jpg" alt="Vacuum Gauge" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/pressure-gauges" title="Vacuum Gauges">Vacuum Gauge</a></div>
  <div>Vacuum gauges are used to measure the pressure in a vacuum system. Measurement can be made with a bourdon tube pressure gauge or diaphragm type gauge. We offer the Wika vacuum gauge as a quality solution for measuring vacuum pressure.</div><br /><br />

 <h2>Pressure Transducer</h2>

  <a href="/category/pressure-transducers"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_19.jpg" alt="Pressure Transducer" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/pressure-transducers" title="Pressure Transducers">Pressure Transducer</a></div>
  <div>What is a pressure transducer? A transducer converts an applied pressure into an electrical analog output signal  that is both linear and proportional to the applied pressure to the transducer. Pressure sensor, pressure transducer, and pressure transmitter are commonly referred to as just pressure transducers. The output electrical signal  from a pressure transducer is sent to computers, PLC's, chart recorders, digital panel meters or other devices that  interpret this signal and use it to display, record, and/or change the pressure in the system being monitored.</div><br /><br />

  <h2>Pressure Regulator</h2>

  <a href="/category/air-regulators"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_21.jpg" alt="Bellofram Pressure Regulator" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/air-regulators" title="Bellofram Pressure Regulators">Bellofram Pressure Regulator</a></div>
  <div>The Bellofram air pressure regulator is used to reduce a higher pressure to a precise lower pressure. Marsh  Bellofram is known for their precision pressure regulators which provide enhanced accuracy, precision control  and maximum stability under adverse conditions. Pressure is changed with a simple manual adjusting knob.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/air-regulator"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_22.jpg" alt="Air Pressure Regulator" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/air-regulator" title="Air Pressure Regulators">Air Pressure Regulator</a></div>
  <div>Air regulators provide controlled, consistent air line pressure as required for specific pneumatic equipment. The  air regulator output pressure is adjusted with a manual knob. Some newer models offer a built in pressure  gauge. Proper compressed air pressure is essential to ensure maximum performance and service life from a  variety of pneumatic tools and equipment.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/combo-air-filter-regulator-lubricator"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_23.jpg" alt="FRL" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/combo-air-filter-regulator-lubricator" title="FRL">FRL</a></div>
  <div>Combining a filter, regulator and lubricator into one assembly is called an FRL. They can be put together in a three piece (F+R+L) or two piece (F/R+L) arrangements. Modular adapters are commonly used to connect each  component together, saving  space and reducing leaks.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/electro-pneumatic-air-regulators-compact"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_24.jpg" alt="Electro Pneumatic" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/electro-pneumatic-air-regulators-compact" title="Electro Pneumatics">Electro Pneumatic</a></div>
  <div>The electro pneumatic regulator or pressure transducer reduces a supply pressure to a regulated output pressure directly proportional to a converted electrical input signal. These voltage or current input signals precisely  control the output air pressure to within 0.1% to 0.5% accuracy for excellent electronic pressure control. Our  electropneumatic regulators and I/P transducer provide solutions to many of your electronic pressure control needs.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/bellofram"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_25.jpg" alt="Bellofram" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/bellofram" title="Marsh Bellofram">Bellofram</a></div>
  <div>Marsh Bellofram has over 40 years experience in the design and manufacture of the air pressure regulator, electro pneumatic, I/P, E/P and related pressure control products. Pressure regulators are critical in OEM and industrial pneumatic applications. Bellofram products are ideal for use in environments where high-­performance and  accuracy are of utmost concern.</div><br /><br />

  <a href="/category/air-regulators"><img src="{$img_prefix}/images/learn-about/h_26.jpg" alt="Ingersoll Rand ARO" class="homeimage" /></a>
  <div class="title"><a href="/category/air-regulators" title="Ingersoll Rand ARO">Ingersoll Rand ARO</a></div>
  <div>For more than 100 years, Ingersoll Rand ARO has been an industrial leader in the design and manufacture of  compressed air equipment. The ARO filter regulator lubricator (FRL) keeps your air supply operating at peak  performance. Proper conditioning of compressed air is essential to maximum performance and service life from  pneumatic tools and equipment.</div><br /><br />

